                            <comment id="17057998" author="anchela" created="Thu, 12 Mar 2020 15:03:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=larsgrefer&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;larsgrefer&quot;&gt;larsgrefer&lt;/a&gt;, thanks for reporting this issue. i will take a look.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17060964" author="anchela" created="Tue, 17 Mar 2020 14:41:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed revision 1875302.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17060967" author="anchela" created="Tue, 17 Mar 2020 14:45:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=larsgrefer&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;larsgrefer&quot;&gt;larsgrefer&lt;/a&gt;, i reduced the priority to minor because &lt;tt&gt;PrincipalRestrictionProvider.writeRestrictions&lt;/tt&gt; is never call in the access control manager. instead the entries (and their restrictions) are extracted and path-based access control is eventually used to write the entries/restrictions. also, i adjusted the summary to describe the issue in an accurate manner. &lt;br/&gt;
but nevertheless, the code was broken (as can be shown by the unit tests i created) and that should be fixed now. thanks for reporting it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
